n = Integer(gets.chomp)
input = gets.chomp
nums = input.split
number = Array.new(n)
number1 = Array.new(n)

for i in 0...n
    number[i] = number1[i] = Integer(nums[i])
end

def sum(a)
    x = 0
    for i in 0...a.length
        x += a[i]
    end
    return x
end

def restore(number1, number)
    for i in 0...number.length
        number1[i] = number[i]
    end
end

c = 0
for i in 0...n
    for j in i...n
        for x in i..j
            if number[x] == 1
                number1[x] = 0
            else
                number1[x] = 1
            end
        end
        if sum(number1) > c
            c = sum(number1)
        end
        restore(number1, number)
    end
end

if n == 1 && number[0] == 1
    puts 0
else
    if c > sum(number)
        puts c
    else
        puts sum(number)
    end
end

n = STDIN.gets.to_i
def remaining(n)
  return 0 if n == 0
  return 1 if n == 1
  return 3 * remaining(n-1)
end
print remaining(n) % (10**6 + 3)

end

#!/usr/bin/ruby
x, y, a, b = gets.split.map(&:to_i)
g = x / x.gcd(y) * y
puts (b / y - (a - 1) / y) - (b / g - (a - 1) / g)

a = gets.split(' ').map(&:to_i)

def ucln(m, n)
    while n != 0
        m, n = n, m % n
    end
    return m
end

def bcnn(m, n)
    return m * n / ucln(m, n)
end

bcnn_value = bcnn(a[0], a[1])

count = (a[3]/bcnn_value).floor - (a[2]/bcnn_value).ceil + 1

puts count

x, y, a, b = gets.chomp.split.map { |x| x.to_i }
k = x.lcm(y)
r = (b - a) / k + 1
puts r

# coding: utf-8

# if __FILE__ == $0
# end

# F(x), factorials of its digits
# F(123) = 1*2*3
# find possible maximum integer
n = gets.to_i
ar = Array.new(11) { 0 }
gets.chomp.split(//).each { |i|
    i = i.to_i
    ar[i] += 1
}

i = 9
j = 2
updated = true
while updated # if equals, indicates no more spread/break op(s) possible
    updated = false
    last_length = ar.length
    # breaking 8 -> 3x 2
    ar[7] += ar[8]
    ar[2] += arar[8] * 3
    ar[8] = 0
    # break 6 -> 3
    ar[5] += ar[6]
    ar[3] += ar[6]
    ar[6] = 0
    # break 4 -> 2x 2
    ar[2] += ar[4]*2
    ar[3] += ar[4]
    ar[4] = 0
    # 1st point to check updated
    updated = ar.length != last_length
    # spread 9->2x 3 if 2's exist
    a9min = [ar[9], ar[2]/2].min
    ar[9] -= a9min
    ar[8] += a9min
    ar[2] -= a9min*2
    ar[3] += a9min*2
    # 2nd point to check updated
    if !updated
        updated = a9min > 0
    end
end

# join'em and print out
buf = []
for j in 2..9
    if ar[j] > 0
        buf << "#{j}"*ar[j]
    end
end

puts buf.reverse.join('')

    puts "\n\n"

  end if local?
  #=================================
end

 end

  red_socks = line[0].to_i
  blue_socks = line[1].to_i

  def fashionable_days(red_socks, blue_socks)
    max_days_different = [red_socks, blue_socks].min
    max_days_same = [red_socks, blue_socks].max - max_days_different
    return max_days_different, max_days_same
  end

  max_days_different, max_days_same = fashionable_days(red_socks, blue_socks)
  puts "#{max_days_different} #{max_days_same}"
else
  puts "Invalid input"
end

	ans += (sum - i).abs
end

puts ans

a, b = gets.split.map(&:to_i)
ans = 0
1.upto(64) do |k|

    m = n ^ (1 << s)
    if a <= m && m <= b
      ans += 1
    end
  end
end
puts ans

        if m <= r && m >= l
            unlucky.push(m)
        end
   end
end

unlucky = unlucky.sort
print unlucky
puts

if !unlucky.empty?
    unlucky_neat.push(unlucky[0])
    for i in 1...unlucky.length
        if unlucky[i] != unlucky[i - 1]
            unlucky_neat.push(unlucky[i])
        end
    end
end
print unlucky_neat
if !unlucky_neat.empty?
    max = (unlucky_neat[0] - l) > (r - unlucky_neat[-1]) ? (unlucky_neat[0] - l) : (r - unlucky_neat[-1])
    for i in 0...unlucky_neat.length - 1
        if unlucky_neat[i + 1] - unlucky_neat[i] - 1 > max
            max = unlucky_neat[i + 1] - unlucky_neat[i] - 1
        end
    end
    puts max
else

    puts max
end

  ans = a if a > ans
end
